org.numenta.nupic.examples.network

Class NetworkAPIDemo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.examples.network.NetworkAPIDemo

  • public class NetworkAPIDemo
extends java.lang.Object
    Demonstrates the Java version of the NuPIC Network API (NAPI) Demo. This demo demonstrates many powerful features of the HTM.java NAPI. Looking at the createBasicNetwork() method demonstrates the conciseness of setting up a basic network. As you can see, the network is constructed in fluent style proceeding from the top-level Network container, to a single Region; then to a single Layer. Layers contain most of the operation logic and are the only constructs that contain algorithm components (i.e. CLAClassifier, Anomaly (the anomaly computer), TemoralMemory, SpatialPooler, and Encoder (actually, a MultiEncoder which can be the parent of many child encoders).
    Author:
    cogmission

      • getSubscriber

        private <any> getSubscriber()
        Demonstrates the composition of a Subscriber (may also use Observer). There are 3 methods one must be concerned with: 

         1. onCompleted(). Called when the stream is exhausted and will be closed.
 2. onError(). Called when there is an underlying exception or error in the processing.
 3. onNext(). Called for each processing cycle of the network. This is the method
 that is overridden to do downstream work in your application.
        Returns:
